<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1555,2012]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1779" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1779" box="[151,630,1591,1616]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobiusculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,630,1591,1616]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,420,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Gobiusculus flavescens</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 
<number box="[564,622,1591,1616]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1779.0">1779</number>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, old citations of this species in the Adriatic are to be considered erroneous (
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic" box="[204,373,1628,1653]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Kovacic, M. (2005) An annotated checklist of the family Gobiidae in the Adriatic Sea. Annales series Historia Naturalis, 15, 21 - 44." type="journal article" year="2005">
Kovačiċ, 
<number box="[313,373,1628,1652]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller" box="[393,545,1628,1652]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Miller, P. J. (1986) Gobiidae. In: Whitehead, P. J. P., Bauchot, M. L., Hureau, J. C., Nielsen, J. &amp; Tortonese, E. (Eds.), Fishes of the North-eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean. Vol. 3. Unesco, Paris, pp. 1015 - 1473." type="book" year="1986">
Miller (
<number box="[478,536,1628,1652]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1986.0">1986</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered doubtful all Mediterranean records, including the report of this species as 
<taxonomicName box="[232,404,1664,1688]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobiusculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruthensparri">
<emphasis box="[232,404,1664,1688]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">G. ruthensparri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Sicily (
<bibRefCitation author="Sanzo" box="[553,689,1663,1687]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Sanzo, L. (1911) Distribuzione delle papille cutanee (organi ciatiformi) e suo valore sistematico nei Gobi. Mitteilungen aus der Zoologischen Station zu Neapel, 20, 249 - 328." type="journal article" year="1911">
Sanzo 
<number box="[630,689,1663,1687]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1911.0">1911</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1555,2012]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authority="Pallas, 1814" authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1814" box="[151,668,1699,1724]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Mesogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="batrachocephalus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,668,1699,1724]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,502,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Mesogobius batrachocephalus</emphasis>
(Pallas, 
<number box="[603,660,1699,1724]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1814.0">1814</number>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, occurs inshore in estuaries and brackish lagoons (rarely in freshwater) of Black Sea, Sea of Azov and Caspian Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Miller" box="[702,846,1735,1759]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Miller, P. J. (1986) Gobiidae. In: Whitehead, P. J. P., Bauchot, M. L., Hureau, J. C., Nielsen, J. &amp; Tortonese, E. (Eds.), Fishes of the North-eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean. Vol. 3. Unesco, Paris, pp. 1015 - 1473." type="book" year="1986">
Miller, 
<number box="[786,846,1735,1759]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It has been recently included in the list of Mediterranean native marine fishes by 
<bibRefCitation box="[505,804,1772,1796]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Abdul Malak, D., Livingstone, S. R., Pollard, D., Polidoro, B. A., Cuttelod, A., Bariche, M., Bilecenoglu, M., Carpenter, K., Bruce, B. C., Francour, P., Goren, M., Kara, M. H., Massuti, E. Papaconstantinou, C. &amp; Tunesi, L. (2011) Overview of the Conservation Status of the Marine Fishes of the Mediterranean Sea. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Malaga, Spain, 61 pp. Ahnelt, H. &amp; Dorda, J. (2004) Gobioid fishes from the north eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean: new records and rarely found species. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 105, 5 - 19." type="book chapter">
Abdul Malak 
<emphasis box="[663,714,1772,1796]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[737,797,1772,1796]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, but no substantiated records of this species exist in the latter sea.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1555,2012]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authority="Pallas, 1814" authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1814" box="[151,637,1843,1868]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Proterorhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,637,1843,1868]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,465,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Proterorhinus marmoratus</emphasis>
(Pallas, 
<number box="[572,629,1843,1868]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1814.0">1814</number>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is primarily a freshwater species occurring in rivers and estuaries of Black Sea, Sea of Azov, Aral and Caspian Sea; it occurs also in rivers of north-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1186,1265,1879,1903]" name="Greece" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Greece</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Miller" box="[1284,1431,1879,1903]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Miller, P. J. (1986) Gobiidae. In: Whitehead, P. J. P., Bauchot, M. L., Hureau, J. C., Nielsen, J. &amp; Tortonese, E. (Eds.), Fishes of the North-eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean. Vol. 3. Unesco, Paris, pp. 1015 - 1473." type="book" year="1986">
Miller, 
<number box="[1372,1431,1879,1903]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Economidis" box="[151,472,1916,1940]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Economidis, P. S. &amp; Miller, P. J. (1990) Systematics of freshwater gobies from Greece (Teleostei: Gobiidae). Journal of Zoology, London, 221, 125 - 170." type="journal article" year="1990">
Economidis &amp; Miller, 
<number box="[412,472,1916,1940]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It has been recently included in the list of Mediterranean native marine fishes by 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,464,1952,1976]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Abdul Malak, D., Livingstone, S. R., Pollard, D., Polidoro, B. A., Cuttelod, A., Bariche, M., Bilecenoglu, M., Carpenter, K., Bruce, B. C., Francour, P., Goren, M., Kara, M. H., Massuti, E. Papaconstantinou, C. &amp; Tunesi, L. (2011) Overview of the Conservation Status of the Marine Fishes of the Mediterranean Sea. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Malaga, Spain, 61 pp. Ahnelt, H. &amp; Dorda, J. (2004) Gobioid fishes from the north eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean: new records and rarely found species. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 105, 5 - 19." type="book chapter">
Abdul Malak 
<emphasis box="[315,368,1952,1976]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[396,456,1952,1976]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, but no substantiated records of this species in the marine environment have been reported so 
<taxonomicName box="[283,317,1988,2012]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Hemiramphidae" genus="Hemiramphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="far">far</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
